1) Display Persons age on .html with css classes applied using [ngClass]
	- boy : Less than 20
	- men : Between 21 to 60
	- old : above 60

	<span [ngClass]="{
    			   'boy': person.age < 20,
    			   'men': person.age <= 60,
			   'old': person.age > 60
  			}">{{ person.name }} ({{ person.age }})
  	</span>



2) Display "Data is loading......" message message on product list component. After loading the data from RESTApi message should be invisible.

3)Validations
 	a) Name should be with the specified length range ie minimum 10 and maximum 20 characters.
		i)  Template Driven Forms	minLength="10"  maxLength="20"
		ii) Reactive Forms		Validators.minLength(10),Validators.maxLength(20)

 	b) Age should be with the specified value range ie minimum 18 and maximum 100
		i)  Template Driven Form	min="18" max="100"
		ii) Reactive Forms		Validators.min(18), Validators.max(100)

	c) Phone number should be of 10 digits using pattern
		i)  Template Driven Form	pattern="[0-9]{10}"
						pattern=/^\d{10}$/

		ii) Reactive Forms		Validators.pattern(/^\d{10}$/)
						Validators.pattern("[0-9]{10}")

	d) Gender should be either "Male", "Female" or "Others" using pattern
		Validators.pattern('^(Male|Female|Others)$')
		

	e) Accept startDate and endDate date. endDate should be minimum 2 years greater then the startDate
		startDate : Date;
		endDate : Date			Validators.min(Date.parse(startDate).getFullYear()+2)
		

	f) expire year
		year=new Date().getFullYear();
		year:['',[Validators.min(1900),Validators.max(this.year+2)]]

	g) Check expire
		checkExpiry(expiry: any){
    			let exp = Date.parse(expiry);    
    			let currDate = Date.now();    
    			if(exp < currDate) {    
     				return 'Yes'    
    			}else{ 
    				returnÂ 'No';    
    			}

	i) Date (dd/mm/yyyy)
		pattern=/^\d{2}//\d{2}//\d{4}$/

